description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 within the field of Infection Prevention and Control and Tissue Viability. This is an exciting time to join a new innovative and expanding team. Both specialities offer high profile agendas, and working corporately, will allow practitioners to develop skills across a wide range of clinical services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will provide an opportunity for a motivated enthusiastic Band 6 nurse with an interest, in infection prevention and control and/or tissue viability to gain valuable experience across a wide variety of disciplines and community settings. The post-holder will have the opportunity to develop their skills within the two specialties, to provide integrated care to users for Tissue Viability and Infection Prevention and Control.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a dynamic team with senior Infection Prevention and Control and Tissue Viability nurses to provide a service for the whole Manchester University Hospital Foundation Trust on all its sites and the community. The post holder will work across the two services on a rotational basis providing integrated care to users across both tissue viability and infection control&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a professional role model you will provide direct and indirect clinical care, ensuring the needs of the patient are central to service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will monitor and improve standards of care through, supervision of practice, clinical audit, evidence based practice, teaching and supporting professional colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
